Summary of Key Points:
    Authentication: Ensure users are who they claim to be (e.g., JWT, OAuth).
    Authorization: Verify that authenticated users have permission to perform specific actions.
    HTTPS: Use secure communication channels to protect data in transit.
    CSRF Protection: Implement tokens to prevent unauthorized actions.
    Rate Limiting: Prevent abuse by limiting the number of requests.
    Device Fingerprinting: Identify and block suspicious devices.
    Logging and Monitoring: Detect and respond to suspicious activities.
